page.title: 01General view of Stickney.
page.content: This area stretches from the northern part of the village of Stickney, to the southern boundary of the village of Stickford. It contains the reclaimed east and west fens and the height of the land ranges from below sea level to nine metres above sea level. The land enclosed by the east and west catchwater drains is predominatly small fields used for grazing, while the land beyond this has been drained to create large arable fields. There are no shopping facilities in the area, although there are three small nurseries, and a "picnic place" with toilets for motorists and local use.There is one garage which provides car servicing and fuel, and an old peoples home.
